properties.name: Dragon's Den
properties.description: Posted by Getbackhomeward435 Esplanade Avenue new orleans, laI saw my first Liquidrone show here. B and I drove to New Orleans that morning to catch some uptown parades, but overslept and missed them. We visited my grandparents and had pizza for a while, then went on to see the show. The bar is up precariously narrow stairs, over a Thai restaurant that is constantly delivering upstairs. The bathroom is downstairs as well, and it seems like an inevitable distaster involving an inebriated person desperately trying to reach the bathroom, and a tray of steaming Thai food. We had already eaten pizza with my grandparents earlier, so we did not order anything. I would like to back and eat there someday. They had charming nooks with red pillows to eat at. I\'m actually not sure if this place is even still open. The walls were covered in old, filmy mirrors that gave the place an incredible ethereal feeling.

properties.name: Red Star
properties.description: Posted by Getbackhomeward222 Laurel St, Baton Rouge, LAThis bar\'s website says "it\'s not your kind of place." This bar caters to the hipster crowd, and it\'s a little too pleased with itself. The bartenders are rude and snotty. It did however, favor the Dimestore Troubadours. When I was 18 and it had just opened, it was a little more relaxed. In fact, even though it is an over-21 bar, the bouncer had a penchant for me and always let me in.
